Description:
Aikido is a modern Japanese martial art that emphasizes self-defense and the harmonious resolution of conflict. It was developed by Morihei Ueshiba, also known as O Sensei, in the early 20th century. The word "Aikido" can be translated as "the way of harmony with the spirit" or "the way of unifying with life energy."

Aikido incorporates techniques derived from various traditional Japanese martial arts, such as jujitsu and swordsmanship, as well as Ueshiba's own philosophical and spiritual beliefs. Unlike many other martial arts, Aikido does not focus on punching or kicking opponents but rather on using their energy and movements against them.
